cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.PL 

This paper is primarily focused on database management systems and their optimization for multi-join queries in memory-resident data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of hash-based equi-joins, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a memory I/O cost model, which involves computational complexity (cs.DC) and performance evaluation (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the conventional wisdom from shared-nothing disk-based systems, which involves parallelization (cs.PL).
